title: England's greatest performances: where does World Cup 2019 semi-final victory over New Zealand rank?
text:
England produced a sensational performance on Saturday to beat the best team on the planet and make it into the final of the 2019 Rugby World Cup.

Eddie Jones' men saw off the All Blacks by 19 points to seven with what was unquestionably one of their best-ever displays, but where exactly does it rank? Here, Mick Cleary ranks his top five England performances...

5. England 12 Australia 10, World Cup quarter-final, Marseille, 2007

When England lost 36-0 to South Africa in their pool match at this tournament, no-one, but no-one could have envisaged that they would be heading north to Paris to contest a semi-final against the host nation after a comprehensive scrum performance saw them account for...
